In article &lt;0X5Op5y00VsLEJ4Udi@andrew.cmu.edu&gt; cfe+@ANDREW.CMU.EDU ("Craig F. Everhart") writes:
&gt;If you're currently calling it both A and B, in different contexts,
&gt;and if you can't stop calling it B, then stop calling it A. 

   I thought I made it very clear in my original article that this is NOT an
acceptable solution! There are very good reasons why I have to be able to
use both names. I'm not a dummy, you know. I am intelligent enough to figure
out that more than one name is a complication, and I have tried too get the
"official" name changed to "ncar" without success. And using a name that no
one can spell, let alone remember, for the name of our major gateway machine
introduces even more complications than I'm facing now.

--Greg

